-- Mexico Stocks: Grupo Elektra, Ica, Grupo Mexico, Consorcio Ara
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-04-12T21:32:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/mexico-stocks-grupo-elektra-ica-grupo-mexico-consorcio-ara.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index  rose 0.5 percent to 39,357.81.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA*)  , the banking and retail
company controlled by billionaire Ricardo Salinas, plunged the
most since 1997, dropping 18 percent to 1,035.92 pesos. The
stock exchange published new rules late yesterday that prevent
shares that are tied up in a company’s derivative transactions
from being included when calculating whether the public float
reaches the minimum level of equity to be on the IPC.  Builders led Mexican stocks higher as Federal Reserve Vice
Chairman  Janet Yellen  and New York Fed President William C.
Dudley endorsed the central bank’s view that borrowing costs are
likely to stay low through 2014.  Empresas Ica SAB (ICA*)  , the country’s biggest
construction company, jumped 4.3 percent to 23.63 pesos.
 Consorcio Ara SAB (ARA*)  , a Mexican homebuilder, climbed 3.4
percent to 4.31 pesos.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, rose 2.3 percent to 40.02 pesos. Copper prices
advanced today on speculation that slower economic growth will
prompt policy makers to add more stimulus measure in China, the
world’s biggest metals consumer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
